gov.nist.secauto.decima.core.assessment

Class ConcurrentAssessmentExecutorFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nist.secauto.decima.core.assessment.ConcurrentAssessmentExecutorFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AssessmentExecutorFactory

    public class ConcurrentAssessmentExecutorFactory
extends Object
implements AssessmentExecutorFactory
    This class provides a mechanism to create new AssessmentExecutor instances that leverage the same Executor instance to execute a sequence of configured Assessment instances against a Document.

    Instances of this class are immutable and can be shared between threads.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ConcurrentAssessmentExecutorFactory

        public ConcurrentAssessmentExecutorFactory(int threads)
        Creates an AssessmentExecutorFactory that uses a ThreadPoolExecutor of the requested size to execute a sequences of configured Assessment instances. A shutdown hook is automatically added that will close this executor when the application ends. For greater control over the executor used or shutdown behavior, use the ConcurrentAssessmentExecutorFactory(Executor) constructor instead.
        Parameters:
        threads - the size of the thread pool
